## 5. Policy Pathways & Scenarios

The market trajectory depends entirely on two unresolved legislative variables.

| Scenario | Federal Action | State Action (Act 54) | Projected Outcome |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **A. Persistent Gridlock** | No Senate vote; EPTC remains expired. | Budget delayed >100 days; Act 54 unfunded. | Further double-digit hikes for 2027; cumulative disenrollment exceeds **200,000**. Risk pool morbidity worsens. |
| **B. Federal Compromise** | Senate passes "CARE Act" (2-yr extension with caps). | Budget delayed; Act 54 unfunded. | Premiums stabilize for lower incomes; complexity increases. Cliff remains for those >400% FPL. |
| **C. State Intervention** | No federal action. | **Act 54 Funded ($50M appropriated).** | Premiums reduced by **9–12%** for 151%–300% FPL cohort. Potential to recoup **40,000+** enrollees. |

